entries.femaleVariant: Launchpad soon... finally.
Theeere you go.
Listen to the hum.
Myers just doesn't let up, does she?
Ugh…
Say we make it, ever wonder what'll happen to Reed?
So Mi?
Just a bad dream, Song…
Just put it outta your mind for now.
Whaddaya think – final stretch, worst behind us?
Still with me, holdin' up?
Uuugh.
Myers is really a go-getter.
Just a bad dream, Song…
[Touch] So Mi?
Whaddaya think – final stretch?
Wonder what'll happen to Reed.
She's made her life about achieving goals, turned herself into a kind of machine.
Wow, you admire her.
That pushing forth, never looking back, it used to piss me off.
Now, wish the future was all I could think about.
As I see it, the worst is always what was, not what'll be.
Huh, an optimist-analyst. How the hell'd you ever hold down your job?
Proper work-life balance. And separation.
Myers is, was done with him. I actually doubt much'll change.
Wish I could fall asleep, never to wake again.
Reed… had a dream about 'im recently.
A repeat, same damn nightmare. 'Bout that same damn train… him dyin' 'cause of what I did.
Put it outta your mind for now.
Actually think Reed forgave you.
Myers gave the order, treated you like her tool.
There's no escapin' remorse.
We all make mistakes.
History, water under the bridge, not worth dwellin' on.
Well, Johnny'd be blunt, if not downright crude. I'll just say, betrayin' a friend? Nothin' worse.
entries.maleVariant: Well, Johnny'd be blunt, if not downright crude. I'll just say, betrayin' a friend? Nothing worse.

entries.femaleVariant: Known this since when?
Meanin' you got other victims on your conscience?
This is all on Myers, her fault.
Betraying a friend? Nothing worse.
Doubt I… can…
I had my orders. I executed.
Rest, please?
Orders from Myers?
Sounds ridiculous now. Years on, he's still her loyal hound, and I can't get away fast enough.
Orders are orders.
You were just following orders.
Age old shit. No reason to dwell on it.
I regret it, I do. But, can't turn back time.
I'd like to just forget.
I coulda said no, coulda warned 'im…
At this point, I'd just rather forget…
Guilt sucks, no escaping remorse.
Nobody's perfect..
Reed's forgiven you, I'm sure.
Neural matrix, V… can only be used once.
Lied to me – what the hell?
Once? How so?
Needed you to help me, needed to be sure you would.
What's left, what'm I supposed to do?
Shit, flat out tricked me. Not a lie I can forgive.
Fuck me.
Could've told me the truth. Woulda helped you anyway.
entries.maleVariant: Coulda told me the truth. Woulda helped you anyway.

entries.femaleVariant: Hot-diggity-fuck. Color me impressed.
Can't forgive you for this, won't.
Song?
I think, I think… I'm gonna die soon…
It's a captive AI from beyond the Wall. Relies on continuous evolution to exist.
[Pick up Songbird] Time to go, So Mi.
Bird took everyone for a ride – Myers, Hansen, Reed, you.
Gonna kick me while I'm down?
Fuck all that. Thing is, you 'n' me're back at square one. Still have that problem – findin' some way to save ourselves.
I'll manage as I have before.
Havin' some fun with me, are ya?
Woman's obsessed, determined to a fault – that earns my respect.
Won't abandon you.
Welp, nice to drop in and shoot some shit, V. High time you woke her, though.
Hey, Song? Almost there.
Coulda chosen differently, can't forgive myself…
Hm, I can't stop thinking about it.
I…
The regret. Wasn't honest with you. I'm sorry…
Tsk, clearly need some help…
Whole sitch haunts Reed to this day, too.
Could be Reed's havin' the same nightmares. Heard it all already, from him.
Want just one thing. To survive, live on.
You're empty-handed, got nothin' to offer – you, the FIA, fuckin' NUS with Myers at its helm. Empty-handed.
Just one dose, one instance of the cure exists. Song decided to keep it, but...
Left me with nothin'…
I see. So Songbird for me, that one dose for you.
Need the cure and the rippers who know how to use it. Mentioned contacts in Europe, personal ones.
Deal. Take her. But don't fuckin' let me die.
entries.maleVariant: Deal. Take 'er. But don't fuckin' let me die.

entries.femaleVariant: Just... take 'er. Got no right to trade her life for anything. Don't wanna.
entries.maleVariant: Just take 'er. I got no right to trade her life for anything. Don't wanna.

entries.femaleVariant: How'm I to know your people'll recover the neural matrix? Any guarantee?
I can't pretend to know this shit inside out. Remember, though, Cynosure's our tech.
Say I survive. What happens to Song, dare I ask?
We'll do our damndest to stop the Blackwall degeneration, look for other ways.
Myers wants Song dead, condemned her already.
Hm... he put his trust in you, for a time.
Trust we then baldly betrayed.
How long've you known this? That only one of us could come out alive?
Couldn't just tell me the truth, Song?
Whoa, hang. What about me?
Mhm.
[Pick up Songbird] Wake the hell up.
Wakie, wakie, end o' the line.
You're ravin'…
Wh-whaddaya mean, Song?
Mind's wanderin', Song. Blackwall, gotta be.
[Touch] Stay awake, Song.
Hey! Don't you doze off on me.
I knew from the start.
Not obvious? You'll fight on, keep looking.
C'mon, time to go.
Reed's not the only one I've betrayed…
In Europe, at Langley, too. The NUSA's specialists are top of the game.
But with this, we're even.
Myers couldn't let 'er escape. If we get her, alive, have 'er in our hands, the NUSA'll be safe, Songbird'll live.
They'll pull the data for you, then operate. Do we have a deal?
I'll free it and end the process. It'll then execute my commands and disintegrate. Irretrievably.
Not the first time somebody's screwed me sideways. Still think I can walk, though.
Nuh-uh, V. Try me first.
Got nothin' I want, nothin' you can give me…
Wanna live on.
You're stronger than I am, V. Stronger than anyone else I know.
Ugh, your attitude to what life sends your way – so touching sometimes.
No, I'm fuckin' serious.
But she stuck it out till the very end… and that commands respect.
Takes character to be a bastard front-to-back and inside-out. Believe me, I know.
Woman dicked you hard 'n' rough, though. Got the right to feel rage, wanna rip her head off.
Damn sorry, Song, I am. But you dicked me first.
What?
[Call Reed] Reed'll take care of you.
Songbird – still want 'er?
Hah, turnin' your back on her now…
Launchpad's in sight, almost there…
Fuck me.
You fuckin' serious?
You serious?
Could always call Reed on the holo.
Hm, think he'd kill me.
Damn, globe-sized ego, V. You mean zilch to 'im. One, just one person he's gunnin' for.
Cynosure – I learned it existed, started delving and--
I know. I'm waiting.
[Help Songbird] Good a place as any.
Deal.
Song's yours, fine. But I don't' want shit from you.
Neural matrix – how'll you get it back?
Song – what'll happen to her?
[Hang up] No deal, not handin' Songbird over.
Ugh. No, no deal. Gave Songbird my word first. Can't break that, won't.
OK, name your price. I'm all ears.
